For this assignment I implimented connect4 using a similar structure I used in the tictactoe assignment
I made the board larger, and made it so players can only place from the top row of the board.

The AI uses a minimax algorithm to decide its moves. It simulates 
possible future board states up to a fixed depth and evaluates 
each position to determine how favorable it is. The AI tries to 
maximize its own score while assuming the opponent will always 
make the best possible move. It also slightly prefers playing in 
the center column since that generally leads to stronger 
positions. This allows it to block immediate threats, take 
winning moves when available, and plan several turns ahead 
instead of playing randomly.
